''See also: [[Hamburger]]''
==English==

===Alternative forms===
*[[burger]]

===Etymology===
From German ''hamburger'', the adjectival form of ''[[Hamburg]]''.

===Noun===
'''hamburger''' (plural: [[hamburgers]])

#A hot [[sandwich]] consisting of a [[patty]] of cooked [[ground]] [[beef]], or a meat substitute, in a sliced [[bun]], sometimes also containing [[salad]] vegetables, [[condiment]]s, or both.
#The patty used in such a sandwich.
#Ground beef, especially that intended to be made into hamburgers.

====Synonyms====
*(''sandwich''): [[beefburger]], [[burger]]
*(''patty'') [[hamburger patty]]

